Load Balancer:
***************
1. Launch 2 Linux Ec2 instance with the user data(server1 userdata put it as "My first webiste on server1 and vice versa on server2")
2. Modify SG by adding HTTP protocol with myIp and dont modify default rule (all traffic)
3. Access the 2 EC2 instances Public IP's on the browser address bar and verify the website is working or not
4. Create Load Balancer (in health check ensure to have /index.html) --> create target group APP-TG and register targets in the TG
5. Access ELB DNS Name(nasty URl).
6. Check the targets in target groups, it should show healthy --> try stickiness(ELB sends requests to One EC2 instance)
   --> configure stickyness
7. Explore path based routing (create 4 instances, 2 with /index.html(App_TG) and 2 with /admin(Admin_TG) and add rules)
     (Select Load Balancer and go to Listeners --> Add condition --> path --> /admin -->
      THEN Forward to --> Admin_TG)
8. Review all ELB Actions and Target Group Actions
9. Stop one EC2 instance and access ELB (It should work)
10. Terminate EC2 instance, ELB and target groups.

user-data for /index.html
#!/bin/bash
yum install httpd -y #install Apache
service httpd start #start Apache
chkconfig httpd on #ON/OFF while EC2 Up/Down
mkdir /var/www/html #Place App location
echo 'Hey!! This is my First Website on EC2! Server-1' > /var/www/html/index.html #App Content

user-data for /admin
#!/bin/bash
yum install httpd -y
service httpd start
chkconfig httpd on
mkdir /var/www/html
echo 'Hey!! This is admin page on EC2! Server-3' > /var/www/html/admin #Path based configuration

